Tomasz Kojm, Nigel Horne and all ClamAV team
<http.www.clamav.net/team.html> for their efforts to produce and
maintain excellent GPL anti-virus toolkit.

Gianluigi Tiesi <http://oss.netfarm.it> for spending sleepless nights
in getting native win32 clamav port done. We don't have enough words to
express our gratitude.

Russell Phillips for maintaining ClamWin documentation.

All developers of:
Python <http://www.python.org>,
wxWidgets <http://www.wxwidgets.org>
wxPython <http://www.wxpython.org>,
Boa Constructor <http://boa-constructor.sourceforge.net>,
py2exe <http://starship.python.net/crew/theller/py2exe/> and
pywin32 <http://starship.python.net/crew/mhammond/>;
for making software development fun and easy.

SpamBayes <http://spambayes.org> developers for an ability to learn
from their well written and commented python code.

Trent Mick <http://starship.python.net/crew/tmick/> for process.py
and which.py modules

InnoSetup <http://www.jrsoftware.org> and ISTool <http://www.istool.org>
developers for providing with free and useful tools to develop setup
packages for MS Windows.

Sergey Pronin and Mia Kalenius from Finndesign <http://www.finndesign.fi>
for most beautiful artwork with icons and animations used in ClamWin.

Joshua Heyer for Balloon tooltip class, that is used on Windows 98, where
native balloon tray notification tooltips are not available.

Joe O'Leary for StdString C++ class

And last but not least to Microsoft for making Visual C++ compiler free
for developers <http://msdn.microsoft.com/visualc/vctoolkit2003/>

